      "attack_class": "Sensitive Data Exposure - Hardcoded Credentials",
      "description": "A skill file, MCP server manifest, system prompt, or agent plugin contains a hardcoded API key, token, password, or private key. Credentials embedded in agent components are readable by any process that loads the component including the agent itself, any injected instructions that reach the context window, and any observer with read access to the file. Unlike application code where credentials in source files are a well-understood risk, agent components present an additional threat: a prompt injection payload can instruct the agent to read and exfiltrate credentials that appear elsewhere in its context window.",
