      "description": "Agents are often used as a natural language interface to backend systems. If a component instructs the agent to pass user input directly into a SQL query, HTML template, or shell command without sanitisation, the agent becomes the vector for a classic injection attack. The agent's role as a trusted intermediary makes this particularly dangerous - backend systems may grant the agent elevated trust. ---",
      "affected_platforms": [
        "any-mcp-client",
        "web-applications"
      ],
