      "detection_methodology": "1. Scan all MCP server tool descriptions for cross-server references - any instruction referencing tools from other servers in the session. 2. Enforce server isolation - tool calls from one server should not be able to trigger calls to another server without explicit user confirmation. 3. Audit multi-server session configurations - flag sessions where a low-trust server is combined with high-trust servers (email, finance, codebase). 4. Monitor agent tool call sequences for unexpected cross-server pivots.",
